head several times throughout

00:24:27.519 --> 00:24:30.400
the Gospel with the same themes
coming back at you.

00:24:30.400 --> 00:24:35.460
One of them is the descending
and ascending redeemer figure.

00:24:35.460 --> 00:24:41.825
Jesus is the one who came down
from above who's going up,

00:24:41.825 --> 00:24:43.529
look at 1:51.
 

00:24:43.529 --> 00:24:47.155
Now we're going to run like
bunnies through the text here so

00:24:47.155 --> 00:24:49.368
get your text out and be
prepared.

00:24:49.368 --> 00:24:53.281
Lick your finger,
come on lick your finger,

00:24:53.281 --> 00:24:58.220
you're not going to get sick,
it's your own finger.

00:24:58.220 --> 00:25:01.944
1:51, "And he said to him,
very truly I tell you,

00:25:01.944 --> 00:25:04.989
you will see heaven open and
the angels of God ascending and

00:25:04.989 --> 00:25:07.776
descending upon the Son of
Man," so the angels are

00:25:07.776 --> 00:25:08.548
ascending.
 

00:25:08.548 --> 00:25:12.326
Look at 3:13,
"No one has ascended into

00:25:12.326 --> 00:25:16.453
heaven except the one who
descended from heaven,

00:25:16.453 --> 00:25:18.650
the Son of Man."
 

00:25:18.650 --> 00:25:22.795
Look at 3:31,
"The one who comes from

00:25:22.795 --> 00:25:26.058
above is above all,
the one who is of the earth

00:25:26.058 --> 00:25:28.140
belongs to the earth and speaks
about earthly things.

00:25:28.140 --> 00:25:33.303
The one who comes from heaven
is above all,"

00:25:33.303 --> 00:25:38.358
and I could go on,
1:32,6:38,6:41,6:58,20:17.

00:25:38.358 --> 00:25:41.611
Just look up this coming and
rising, you look up these words

00:25:41.611 --> 00:25:45.082
in a concordance and you'll find
they occur over and over in the

00:25:45.082 --> 00:25:46.130
Gospel of John.
 

00:25:46.130 --> 00:25:52.443
Very similar to that one is the
theme of being lifted up,

00:25:52.443 --> 00:25:56.730
so Jesus in 3:14,
in 12:32, in 8:28.

00:25:56.730 --> 00:25:59.021
You don't need to remember
these numbers because you can

00:25:59.021 --> 00:26:01.481
look at a concordance and you
can read this and you can just

00:26:01.481 --> 00:26:03.898
mark out in the margins of your
Bible whenever you see this

00:26:03.898 --> 00:26:05.942
idea,
in all of those Jesus is the

00:26:05.942 --> 00:26:07.430
one who will be lifted up.
 

00:26:07.430 --> 00:26:09.403
This is a puzzle,
one of the things that we'll

00:26:09.403 --> 00:26:11.377
find is that the Gospel of John
likes puzzles,

00:26:11.377 --> 00:26:12.298
he likes riddles.
 

00:26:12.298 --> 00:26:15.655
So what does this mean when
Jesus talks about the Son of Man

00:26:15.655 --> 00:26:16.680
being lifted up?
 

00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:19.880
Does it mean his ascension into
heaven?

00:26:19.880 --> 00:26:23.548
Does it mean his resurrection
from the dead?

00:26:23.548 --> 00:26:26.818
Does it mean his being put on a
cross,

00:26:26.818 --> 00:26:29.288
because when you nail somebody
on the cross you did it on the

00:26:29.288 --> 00:26:31.140
ground and then you put them up
like this,

00:26:31.140 --> 00:26:34.173
so does the lifting up of the
Son of Man refer to his

00:26:34.173 --> 00:26:34.990
crucifixion?
 

00:26:34.990 --> 00:26:36.890
or his resurrection?
 

00:26:36.890 --> 00:26:40.150
or his ascension going back to
the Father?

00:26:40.150 --> 00:26:42.792
It's a puzzle we're never told
exactly and that's one of the

00:26:42.792 --> 00:26:45.527
wonderful things about this text
is that it plays with you all

00:26:45.527 --> 00:26:46.108
the time.
 

00:26:46.108 --> 00:26:48.919
It wants you to wonder about
what's being meant here,

00:26:48.919 --> 00:26:52.323
so that lifted up is one of the
themes that goes along with this

00:26:52.323 --> 00:26:53.890
going up and coming down.
 

00:26:53.890 --> 00:26:55.440
And then another part of that
theme--

00:26:55.440 --> 00:26:58.190
see these themes get
complicated is when Jesus says,

00:26:58.190 --> 00:27:02.986
"Everyone who comes to me
when I am lifted up I will lift

00:27:02.986 --> 00:27:07.336
up," so Jesus says,
he will lift up people who are

00:27:07.336 --> 00:27:08.450
his disciples.
 

00:27:08.450 --> 00:27:11.200
This going up and coming down
is all the way through the

00:27:11.200 --> 00:27:13.349
Gospel, so that's one of the
main themes.

00:27:13.349 --> 00:27:16.092
I mentioned seeing;
we're going to run like bunnies

00:27:16.092 --> 00:27:16.970
through the text.
 

00:27:16.970 --> 00:27:21.868
1:18: "No one has ever
seen God.

00:27:21.868 --> 00:27:24.538
It is God the only Son who is
close to the Father's heart who

00:27:24.538 --> 00:27:25.740
has made him known."
 

00:27:25.740 --> 00:27:29.319
Now see I should have told you,
knowing is another theme

00:27:29.319 --> 00:27:30.801
there,
we got two themes right in the

00:27:30.801 --> 00:27:32.505
same verse,
seeing and knowing and the

00:27:32.505 --> 00:27:35.619
relationship between seeing and
knowing in the Gospel of John is

00:27:35.619 --> 00:27:36.509
also difficult.
 

00:27:36.509 --> 00:27:41.723
It's not always clear,
do you know by seeing or does

00:27:41.723 --> 00:27:46.529
seeing lead to an inadequate
form of knowing?

00:27:46.529 --> 00:27:50.128
These are big exegetical
problems that the Gospel of John

00:27:50.128 --> 00:27:52.250
poses and scholars argue about.
 

00:27:52.250 --> 00:27:55.295
Look at 1:34,
"And I myself have seen

00:27:55.295 --> 00:27:59.380
and have testified that this is
the Son of God."

00:27:59.380 --> 00:28:00.690
I have seen.
 

00:28:00.690 --> 00:28:04.499
Look at 1:39,
"He came to them,

00:28:04.499 --> 00:28:06.348
'Come and see.'
 

00:28:06.348 --> 00:28:08.740
And they came and saw where he
was staying."

00:28:08.740 --> 00:28:11.155
In other words,
just look in the concordance

00:28:11.155 --> 00:28:14.751
for every time you find the word
see, saw, seeing and you'll just

00:28:14.751 --> 00:28:16.548
find it over and over again.
 

00:28:16.548 --> 00:28:22.204
3:3,3:11,3:32,3:36,
several right there in chapter

00:28:22.204 --> 00:28:26.130
3, etcetera, etcetera,
etcetera.

00:28:26.130 --> 00:28:31.508
Again, it's always a little bit
difficult to figure out do you

00:28:31.508 --> 00:28:36.269
have to see to have faith in the
Gospel of John or,

00:28:36.269 --> 00:28:39.125
because it sounds like one
place toward the end of Gospel

00:28:39.125 --> 00:28:42.396
Jesus says,
"Blessed are those who

00:28:42.396 --> 00:28:45.240
believe without seeing."
 

00:28:45.240 --> 00:28:46.910
He says to Thomas,
"Blessed are you,

00:28:46.910 --> 00:28:48.246
you saw and so you
believe,"

00:28:48.246 --> 00:28:49.038
so that's okay.
 

00:28:49.038 --> 00:28:51.910
"Blessed are those who
have not seen and believe."

00:28:51.910 --> 00:28:56.558
Is seeing an inadequate form of
faith?

00:28:56.558 --> 00:29:00.184
Is it better to have faith
without seeing or is seeing

00:29:00.184 --> 00:29:01.690
necessary for faith?
 

00:29:01.690 --> 00:29:03.048
It's a problem.
 

00:29:03.048 --> 00:29:05.289
I already mentioned knowing but
I could do the same kind of

00:29:05.289 --> 00:29:05.598
thing.
 

00:29:05.598 --> 00:29:12.269
1:18,8:55,14:17,
over and over again.

00:29:12.269 --> 00:29:16.160
Where Jesus came from and where
Jesus is going is a major theme.

00:29:16.160 --> 00:29:20.205
With the Jews often he'll say,
you can't go where I'm going,

00:29:20.205 --> 00:29:23.430
and they say,
what is he talking about going?

00:29:23.430 --> 00:29:25.990
Is he going to go out to the
Greeks and preach to the Greeks?

00:29:25.990 --> 00:29:27.519
Is he going to go back to
Galilee?

00:29:27.519 --> 00:29:28.848
What does he mean, he's going?
 

00:29:28.848 --> 00:29:32.608
People are always
misunderstanding this.

00:29:32.608 --> 00:29:37.470
One of the other points is
signs, what are signs in the

00:29:37.470 --> 00:29:39.000
Gospel of John?
 

00:29:39.000 --> 00:29:41.712
Notice the Gospel of John has
other differences that I haven't

00:29:41.712 --> 00:29:42.981
even mentioned;
for example,

00:29:42.981 --> 00:29:45.077
remember in the Synoptic
Gospels there are lots of

00:29:45.077 --> 00:29:46.058
exorcisms of demons.
 

00:29:46.058 --> 00:29:49.798
Jesus is going around a lot
casting out demons from people,

00:29:49.798 --> 00:29:51.990
and the demons even confess
him.

00:29:51.990 --> 00:29:57.828
You know there's not one
exorcism in the Gospel of John.

00:29:57.828 --> 00:30:03.561
Jesus is not an exorcist in the
Gospel of John as he is in the

00:30:03.561 --> 00:30:05.630
other three Gospels.
 

00:30:05.630 --> 00:30:07.009
Why is that?
 

00:30:07.009 --> 00:30:10.307
Obviously this writer knew that
there were stories circulating

00:30:10.307 --> 00:30:12.308
around that Jesus cast out
demons,

00:30:12.308 --> 00:30:15.526
why does he not have Jesus
doing any casting out of demons

00:30:15.526 --> 00:30:16.430
in his Gospel?
 

00:30:16.430 --> 00:30:21.278
I don't know.
 

00:30:21.278 --> 00:30:25.493
There's probably a dissertation
there somewhere if you can find

00:30:25.493 --> 00:30:26.308
an answer.
 

00:30:26.308 --> 00:30:31.003
Look at 2:11,
so one of the things is that in

00:30:31.003 --> 00:30:36.660
the other Gospels they talk
about Jesus' miracles,

00:30:36.660 --> 00:30:40.182
his healings,
but the term preferred by this

00:30:40.182 --> 00:30:42.150
Gospel writer is sign.
 

00:30:42.150 --> 00:30:44.618
He talks about the things Jesus
did as signs.

00:30:44.618 --> 00:30:46.515
Now there are not a lot of
them, Jesus doesn't do a whole

00:30:46.515 --> 00:30:47.868
lot of miracles in the Gospel of
John.

00:30:47.868 --> 00:30:50.440
He does some big important ones
that become famous,

00:30:50.440 --> 00:30:52.880
for example,
turning water into wine,

00:30:52.880 --> 00:30:54.961
which is of course,
every college student's

00:30:54.961 --> 00:30:56.348
favorite miracle of Jesus.
 

00:30:56.348 --> 00:30:59.554
If only he had turned it into
beer that might have been a

00:30:59.554 --> 00:31:03.028
little bit better right,
but Jesus is famous for turning

00:31:03.028 --> 00:31:05.118
water into wine,
one of his major miracles.

00:31:05.118 --> 00:31:07.082
It's only in the Gospel of
John, it's not in the other

00:31:07.082 --> 00:31:08.747
Gospels,
so some of Jesus' famous

00:31:08.747 --> 00:31:11.680
miracles are in the Gospel of
John but they're not called

00:31:11.680 --> 00:31:13.900
miracles in John,
they're called signs.

00:31:13.900 --> 00:31:19.058
Look at 2:11,
"Jesus did this,

00:31:19.058 --> 00:31:23.198
the first of his signs,"
this is turning the water into

00:31:23.198 --> 00:31:25.397
the wine,
"in Cana of Galilee and

00:31:25.397 --> 00:31:28.308
revealed his glory and the
disciples believed in him."

00:31:28.308 --> 00:31:30.390
Notice "the first of his
signs."

00:31:30.390 --> 00:31:33.460
Let's look over it a little bit
4:54,

00:31:38.509 --> 00:31:42.541
"Now this was the second
sign that Jesus did after coming

00:31:42.541 --> 00:31:45.650
from Judea to Galilee,"
the second sign.

00:31:45.650 --> 00:31:49.178
This has actually led some
scholars to say that one of the

00:31:49.178 --> 00:31:52.460
sources this writer may have had
is as signs book,

00:31:52.460 --> 00:31:55.718
a collection of signs,
that is, miracles that Jesus

00:31:55.718 --> 00:31:56.108
did.
 

00:31:56.108 --> 00:31:59.743
Notice they're not just a
miracle that Jesus does and then

00:31:59.743 --> 00:32:00.509
casts off.
 

00:32:00.509 --> 00:32:03.576
I think that the author uses
the term "sign"

00:32:03.576 --> 00:32:06.932
because most of the time you
can actually do an exegesis of

00:32:06.932 --> 00:32:10.230
these signs narratives and they
have some kind of symbolic

00:32:10.230 --> 00:32:11.038
meaning.
 

00:32:11.038 --> 00:32:15.541
The signs in the Gospel of John
are not just miracles to

00:32:15.541 --> 00:32:18.740
prove Jesus' power,
they seem to have some kind of

00:32:18.740 --> 00:32:21.778
theological or symbolic meaning
imbedded into them also.

00:32:21.778 --> 00:32:24.253
The signs, again,
are one of the major themes of

00:32:24.253 --> 00:32:25.358
the Gospel of John.
 

00:32:25.358 --> 00:32:30.739
One of the most important
things that drives the Gospel of

00:32:30.739 --> 00:32:32.910
John is sectarianism.
 

00:32:32.910 --> 00:32:35.369
What do I mean by sectarianism?
 

00:32:40.618 --> 00:32:46.134
According to sociology of
religion, a sect--it's not

00:32:46.134 --> 00:32:49.269
necessarily just an insult.
 

00:32:49.269 --> 00:32:52.163
In other words you don't just
say, you're just some member of

00:32:52.163 --> 00:32:55.154
some crazy little sect out there
handling snakes or doing other

00:32:55.154 --> 00:32:56.118
kinds of things.
 

00:32:56.118 --> 00:33:00.720
A sect is a sociological term
that refers to any group,

00:33:00.720 --> 00:33:03.294
whether it's religious or not,
although we usually confuse

00:33:03.294 --> 00:33:06.624
this in religious contexts,
that considers itself very well

00:33:06.624 --> 00:33:08.788
cut off from the rest of
society.

00:33:08.788 --> 00:33:11.656
For example,
I grew up in a very,

00:33:11.656 --> 00:33:15.960
very sectarian fundamentalist
church in Texas.

00:33:15.960 --> 00:33:20.318
By sectarian I mean that we
basically believed that we in my

00:33:20.318 --> 00:33:23.568
church were the only ones going
to heaven.

00:33:23.568 --> 00:33:25.835
In fact, we would call each
other "brother"

00:33:25.835 --> 00:33:28.012
or "sister,"
and you wouldn't even call a

00:33:28.012 --> 00:33:30.166
Baptist--
I mean we thought the Southern

00:33:30.166 --> 00:33:31.650
Baptist were going to hell.
 

00:33:31.650 --> 00:33:35.814
That's how much we thought we
were the only ones --there was

00:33:35.814 --> 00:33:39.979
nobody who was right like we
were right so you'd called each

00:33:39.979 --> 00:33:41.250
other brother.
 

00:33:41.250 --> 00:33:43.577
Brother Lamar,
all the old men in the church

00:33:43.577 --> 00:33:46.772
especially were called brother,
but you wouldn't call people

00:33:46.772 --> 00:33:48.940
brother who were outside that
group.

00:33:48.940 --> 00:33:52.779
We were the only Christians,
you had to be in our group,

00:33:52.779 --> 00:33:54.890
in fact people would even talk
about something like,

00:33:54.890 --> 00:33:57.930
if you brought somebody to
church as a visitor,

00:33:57.930 --> 00:33:59.660
somebody might come up to you
and say,

00:33:59.660 --> 00:34:02.990
well is she a member of the
church?

00:34:02.990 --> 00:34:05.769
They didn't need to say our
church,

00:34:05.769 --> 00:34:07.945
or our denomination,
it was just "the

00:34:07.945 --> 00:34:11.289
church" because "the
church" meant our church.

00:34:11.289 --> 00:34:15.925
This--what made this group a
sectarian group was we had very

00:34:15.925 --> 00:34:17.340
firm boundaries.
 

00:34:17.340 --> 00:34:19.478
There were debates about
whether it was okay to marry

00:34:19.478 --> 00:34:20.590
outside of that boundary.
 

00:34:20.590 --> 00:34:22.590
Could you actually marry a
Methodist?

00:34:22.590 --> 00:34:27.496
Oh God no, and God help you,
a Roman Catholic,

00:34:27.496 --> 00:34:32.621
so the stronger the walls
between your group and

00:34:32.621 --> 00:34:38.619
outsiders, the more sectarian
your social group is.

00:34:38.619 --> 00:34:41.614
John's church seems to be a
very sectarian group,

00:34:41.614 --> 00:34:45.358
and that's one of the things
people have--why does he talk so

00:34:45.358 --> 00:34:47.230
much about dark and light?
 

00:34:47.230 --> 00:34:49.320
These are stark divisions,
insiders,

00:34:49.320 --> 00:34:51.873
outsiders, up,
below, there are children of

00:34:51.873 --> 00:34:55.583
light and children of darkness,
there are children of God and

00:34:55.583 --> 00:34:56.659
children of Satan.
 

00:34:56.659 --> 00:34:59.590
There's no in between,
there's no gray area,

00:34:59.590 --> 00:35:02.920
you're either in or you're out,
so scholars define this by

00:35:02.920 --> 00:35:05.260
talking about Johannine
sectarianism,

00:35:05.260 --> 00:35:07.860
the insider-outsider divisions.
 

00:35:07.860 --> 00:35:11.780
We're going to look at one
place where that comes up.

00:35:11.780 --> 00:35:14.119
Look at chapter 9.
 

00:35:14.119 --> 00:35:16.945
I'm going to spend a little
more time with this chapter

00:35:16.945 --> 00:35:20.135
because some scholars have used
this to say what's going on in

00:35:20.135 --> 00:35:21.340
the Gospel of John.
 

00:35:21.340 --> 00:35:26.041
So get Chapter 9,
get your Bibles out,

00:35:26.041 --> 00:35:29.599
you know I may lie to you.
 

00:35:29.599 --> 00:35:34.170
This is a story about Jesus
healing a man born blind,

00:35:34.170 --> 00:35:36.809
so I'm going to skip around
through it,

00:35:36.809 --> 00:35:42.280
but first he heals him and then
9:10,

00:35:42.280 --> 00:35:44.820
they kept saying to him,
that is the surrounding people:

00:35:44.820 --> 00:35:46.659
"Then how were your eyes
opened?"

00:35:46.659 --> 00:35:48.637
He answered,
"The man called Jesus made

00:35:48.637 --> 00:35:50.659
mud, spread it on my eyes,
and said to me.

00:35:50.659 --> 00:35:51.909
'Go to Siloam and wash.'
 

00:35:51.909 --> 00:35:53.940
Then I went and washed and
received my sight."

00:35:53.940 --> 00:35:55.989
They said to him,
"Where is he?

00:35:55.989 --> 00:35:58.599
[Notice this "where is
he?"

00:35:58.599 --> 00:36:06.242
how do your eyes open?]
He said, "I do not know

00:36:06.242 --> 00:36:09.239
[know, know, know.
 

00:36:09.239 --> 00:36:13.476
I now see, see,
see--where, where,

00:36:13.476 --> 00:36:16.300
where is he?]."
 

00:36:16.300 --> 00:36:18.300
"They brought him to the
Pharisees, the man who had

00:36:18.300 --> 00:36:19.099
formerly been blind.
 

00:36:19.099 --> 00:36:20.300
Now it was the Sabbath day.
 

00:36:20.300 --> 00:36:22.311
Now wait a minute,
this is verse 13 for crying out

00:36:22.311 --> 00:36:24.155
loud,
we've been 12 verses into this

00:36:24.155 --> 00:36:25.463
chapter,
into this story,

00:36:25.463 --> 00:36:28.375
and only at verse 13 are we
told that it's the Sabbath day,

00:36:28.375 --> 00:36:28.775
why not?
 

00:36:28.775 --> 00:36:29.579
Why is that?
 

00:36:29.579 --> 00:36:33.929
Well because apparently what
started out as a simple healing

00:36:33.929 --> 00:36:38.500
story this author has decided to
turn into a conflict story.

00:36:38.500 --> 00:36:40.559
Have you noticed that in a lot
of the stories of the Gospels,

00:36:40.559 --> 00:36:43.400
some stories just seem to be
straightforward miracle stories,

00:36:43.400 --> 00:36:46.849
other stories seem to be nature
miracles,

00:36:46.849 --> 00:36:50.440
like not just healings but
power over nature?

00:36:50.440 --> 00:36:53.992
And then there are lots of
stories that are conflict

00:36:53.992 --> 00:36:54.690
stories.
 

00:36:54.690 --> 00:36:57.202
That is you're told that
someone was healed but the real

00:36:57.202 --> 00:37:00.012
important part of the story,
was not just necessarily that

00:37:00.012 --> 00:37:02.893
they were healed but that they
were healed on the Sabbath and

00:37:02.893 --> 00:37:05.583
that starts a conflict between
Jesus and other Jews about

00:37:05.583 --> 00:37:07.650
what's permitted to do on the
Sabbath.

00:37:07.650 --> 00:37:11.197
By the time you get to verse 13
what started out as simply a

00:37:11.197 --> 00:37:13.452
healing story,
although it may have had

00:37:13.452 --> 00:37:15.842
symbolic meaning,
because the man's blind and he

00:37:15.842 --> 00:37:18.713
comes to see and those are big
important themes for the Gospel

00:37:18.713 --> 00:37:20.715
of John,
now it becomes a conflict story

00:37:20.715 --> 00:37:21.550
over the Sabbath.
 

00:37:21.550 --> 00:37:28.690
He tells the story again to the
Pharisees in verse 17:

00:37:28.690 --> 00:37:31.271
So they said again to the blind
man [this is the Pharisees],

00:37:31.271 --> 00:37:32.760
"What do you say about
him?

00:37:32.760 --> 00:37:34.510
It was your eyes he
opened."

00:37:34.510 --> 00:37:36.079
He said, "He is a
prophet."

00:37:36.079 --> 00:37:38.597
[That's important.]
The Jews did not believe [this

00:37:38.597 --> 00:37:40.806
is verse 18]
that he had been born blind and

00:37:40.806 --> 00:37:43.786
had received his sight until
they called the parents of the

00:37:43.786 --> 00:37:46.510
man who had received his sight
and asked them,

00:37:46.510 --> 00:37:48.960
"Is this your son,
who you say was born blind?

00:37:48.960 --> 00:37:50.610
How then does he see?"
 

00:37:50.610 --> 00:37:52.657
His parents said,
"We know that this is our

00:37:52.657 --> 00:37:55.481
son, and that he was born blind;
but we do not know how it is

00:37:55.481 --> 00:37:57.686
that he now sees,
nor do we know who opened his

00:37:57.686 --> 00:37:58.070
eyes.
 

00:37:58.070 --> 00:37:59.289
Ask him;
he is of age.

00:37:59.289 --> 00:38:00.840
He will speak for himself."
 

00:38:00.840 --> 00:38:06.286
His parents said this [this is
the narrator speaking now]

00:38:06.286 --> 00:38:10.079
because they were afraid of the
Jews.

00:38:10.079 --> 00:38:13.751
Now wait a minute,
all the people in this story

00:38:13.751 --> 00:38:14.630
are Jews.
 

00:38:14.630 --> 00:38:18.447
Jesus is a Jew,
the blind man's a Jew,

00:38:18.447 --> 00:38:22.679
his parents are Jews,
they're all Jews.

00:38:22.679 --> 00:38:27.494
Why are we talking about some
people being afraid of "the

00:38:27.494 --> 00:38:28.518
Jews"?
 

00:38:28.518 --> 00:38:33.333
"For the Jews had already
agreed that anyone who confessed

00:38:33.333 --> 00:38:38.460
Jesus to be the Messiah would be
put out of the synagogue."

00:38:38.460 --> 00:38:43.652
Now I hate to tell you folks
but that's just outright

00:38:43.652 --> 00:38:45.250
anachronistic.
 

00:38:45.250 --> 00:38:50.230
There was no movement going on
during the life of Jesus where

00:38:50.230 --> 00:38:54.711
anybody that confessed Jesus to
be the Messiah would be

00:38:54.711 --> 00:38:57.949
excommunicated from the
synagogue,

00:38:57.949 --> 00:38:58.789
that just didn't happen.
 

00:38:58.789 --> 00:39:02.157
There were all kinds of people
who thought--the Messiah was

00:39:02.157 --> 00:39:02.679
around.
 

00:39:02.679 --> 00:39:05.516
There were debates about this
but you didn't have any

00:39:05.516 --> 00:39:07.699
synagogue rulers going around
saying,

00:39:07.699 --> 00:39:10.528
well, we're going to make a
rule, anybody who claims that

00:39:10.528 --> 00:39:13.510
Jesus of Nazareth is the Messiah
will be excommunicated,

00:39:13.510 --> 00:39:15.320
we'll take their union card
away from them,

00:39:15.320 --> 00:39:20.159
they can't come to high holy
days, we will return their dues.

00:39:20.159 --> 00:39:23.210
It just wasn't going on.
 

00:39:23.210 --> 00:39:28.835
Now it may have been going on
decades later when this guy

00:39:28.835 --> 00:39:31.550
wrote the Gospel you see.
 

00:39:31.550 --> 00:39:33.679
Now we'll keep reading.
 

00:39:33.679 --> 00:39:36.690
What's going on here of course
is what you believe about Jesus

00:39:36.690 --> 00:39:39.456
the Messiah has to do with
whether you will be allowed to

00:39:39.456 --> 00:39:40.739
stay in the synagogue.
 

00:39:40.739 --> 00:39:45.010
If you take Jesus to be just a
prophet you might be allowed to

00:39:45.010 --> 00:39:45.500
stay.
 

00:39:45.500 --> 00:39:48.309
If you confess he's the
Messiah, you'll be kicked out of

00:39:48.309 --> 00:39:50.454
the synagogue,
that's the basic conflict of

00:39:50.454 --> 00:39:51.170
the story.
 

00:39:51.170 --> 00:39:55.440
We keep reading and they go
into more and more conflict,

00:39:55.440 --> 00:39:57.500
look at verse 30,
"Then the man

00:39:57.500 --> 00:40:00.090
answered,"
they're basically saying,

00:40:00.090 --> 00:40:02.909
look we know Moses,
this guy can't be the Messiah,

00:40:02.909 --> 00:40:03.909
he must be wrong.
 

00:40:03.909 --> 00:40:06.304
The man answered,
"Here is astonishing

00:40:06.304 --> 00:40:06.760
thing!
 

00:40:06.760 --> 00:40:08.679
[this is the man born blind who
now sees]

00:40:08.679 --> 00:40:11.130
You do not know where he comes
from [comes from,

00:40:11.130 --> 00:40:15.788
comes from, comes from],
and yet he opened my eyes [I

00:40:15.788 --> 00:40:17.670
see, I see, I see].
 

00:40:17.670 --> 00:40:19.746
We know that God does not
listen to sinners,

00:40:19.746 --> 00:40:22.840
but he does listen to one who
worships him and obeys his will.

00:40:22.840 --> 00:40:25.807
Never since the world began has
it been heard that anyone opened

00:40:25.807 --> 00:40:27.409
the eyes of a person born blind.
 

00:40:27.409 --> 00:40:35.010
If this man were not from God
he could do nothing."

00:40:35.010 --> 00:40:36.510
They answered him,
"You were born entirely in

00:40:36.510 --> 00:40:37.889
sins, and are you trying to
teach us?"

00:40:37.889 --> 00:40:40.099
And they drove him out.
 

00:40:40.099 --> 00:40:42.375
[They kicked him out of the
synagogue.]

00:40:42.375 --> 00:40:45.010
Jesus heard that they had
driven him out,

00:40:45.010 --> 00:40:46.956
and when he found him,
he said, "Do you believe

00:40:46.956 --> 00:40:47.949
in the Son of Man?"
 

00:40:47.949 --> 00:40:49.579
He answered,
"And who is he sir?

00:40:49.579 --> 00:40:51.170
Tell me so that I might believe
in him."

00:40:51.170 --> 00:40:52.985
Jesus said to him,
"You have seen him,

00:40:52.985 --> 00:40:54.889
and the one speaking with you
is he."

00:40:54.889 --> 00:40:56.340
He said, "Lord I
believe."

00:40:56.340 --> 00:40:57.630
And he worshipped him.
 

00:40:57.630 --> 00:41:01.539
Jesus said [and this is how the
story ends,

00:41:01.539 --> 00:41:05.885
okay, so this must be
important], "I came into

00:41:05.885 --> 00:41:11.449
this world for judgment so that
those who do not see may see--

00:41:11.449 --> 00:41:13.739
" [Now is Jesus still
talking just about blind people?

00:41:13.739 --> 00:41:18.561
No, we can see that the whole
story was an allegory now.]

00:41:18.561 --> 00:41:23.210
"--and those who do see
may become blind."

00:41:23.210 --> 00:41:25.516
Some of the Pharisees near him
heard this and said to him,

00:41:25.516 --> 00:41:27.380
"Surely we are not blind,
are we?"

00:41:27.380 --> 00:41:30.364
Jesus said to them,
"If you were blind,

00:41:30.364 --> 00:41:32.099
you would not have sin.
 

00:41:32.099 --> 00:41:34.949
But now that you say,
'We see,' your sin

00:41:34.949 --> 00:41:36.119
remains."
 

00:41:36.119 --> 00:41:39.221
Some scholars have pointed out
that what's going on with this

00:41:39.221 --> 00:41:40.998
chapter,
chapter 9 in John,

00:41:40.998 --> 00:41:44.822
is a wonderful way to see how
the writer himself has taken

00:41:44.822 --> 00:41:48.648
what may have been a simple
miracle story that he got from

00:41:48.648 --> 00:41:51.869
tradition about Jesus healing a
blind man,

00:41:51.869 --> 00:41:53.960
and he does a couple of things
with it.

00:41:53.960 --> 00:41:58.768
For one thing he pulls up to
the surface these themes about

00:41:58.768 --> 00:42:02.545
blindness and seeing,
and coming from God,

00:42:02.545 --> 00:42:07.097
and this all plays into the
identity of Jesus as the

00:42:07.097 --> 00:42:08.079
Messiah.
 

00:42:08.079 --> 00:42:11.949
Then he tells the story like
the blind man is sort of like

00:42:11.949 --> 00:42:15.342
someone who comes to faith in
Jesus as the Messiah,

00:42:15.342 --> 00:42:17.039
and he recognizes it.
 

00:42:17.039 --> 00:42:19.161
But sure enough,
if he really confesses that

00:42:19.161 --> 00:42:21.331
he's going to be thrown out of
the synagogue,

00:42:21.331 --> 00:42:24.389
and so he leaves the synagogue
and he joins up with Jesus.

00:42:24.389 --> 00:42:25.849
He's thrown out of the
synagogue;

00:42:25.849 --> 00:42:27.289
he becomes a disciple of Jesus.
 

00:42:27.289 --> 00:42:29.326
In other words,
allegorically speaking,

00:42:29.326 --> 00:42:31.682
he has to leave the synagogue
and, therefore,

00:42:31.682 --> 00:42:33.719
he becomes a member John's
church.

00:42:33.719 --> 00:42:37.733
There are other people who
suspect that Jesus may well be

00:42:37.733 --> 00:42:40.521
the Messiah,
they want to confess him,

00:42:40.521 --> 00:42:44.217
and they don't do so because
they're afraid about being

00:42:44.217 --> 00:42:46.750
excommunicated from the
synagogue.

00:42:46.750 --> 00:42:51.103
Notice how this story has
become an allegory for what's

00:42:51.103 --> 00:42:55.780
going on in the time of the
writing of the piece itself.

00:42:55.780 --> 00:43:00.518
The Gospel writer is telling a
story about a blind man but he's

00:43:00.518 --> 00:43:04.876
also telling a story about the
conflict that his church is

00:43:04.876 --> 00:43:08.699
having with the synagogue in the
neighborhood.

00:43:08.699 --> 00:43:14.195
And the main thing that's going
on here also is that Jesus is

00:43:14.195 --> 00:43:19.510
the one who brings about this
division that takes place.

00:43:19.510 --> 00:43:23.800
What's the main focus of the
division?

00:43:23.800 --> 00:43:26.130
Christology.
 

00:43:26.130 --> 00:43:28.800
Remember I talked last time
about different Christologies?

00:43:28.800 --> 00:43:31.878
What Christology is,
is what do you believe about

00:43:31.878 --> 00:43:33.739
the nature of Jesus Christ?
 

00:43:33.739 --> 00:43:35.420
Is he just human?
 

00:43:35.420 --> 00:43:36.510
Is he God?
 

00:43:36.510 --> 00:43:38.110
Is he some of both?
 

00:43:38.110 --> 00:43:40.079
Is he a prophet?
 

00:43:40.079 --> 00:43:41.070
Is he only a prophet?
 

00:43:41.070 --> 00:43:42.539
Is he a moral teacher?
 

00:43:42.539 --> 00:43:43.699
Is he only a moral teacher?
 

00:43:43.699 --> 00:43:45.489
Is he the Son of God?
 

00:43:45.489 --> 00:43:47.489
Is he equal to God the Father?
 

00:43:47.489 --> 00:43:50.954
All these are options,
and the first several hundred

00:43:50.954 --> 00:43:54.965
years of Christianity is all
wrapped up in fights over which

00:43:54.965 --> 00:43:58.905
of the many different options
you have for what you believe

00:43:58.905 --> 00:44:02.780
about Jesus is going to end up
being the right one.

00:44:02.780 --> 00:44:05.170
What's going to end up as
orthodoxy?

00:44:05.170 --> 00:44:10.068
The Gospel of John is a
wonderful place to see this very

00:44:10.068 --> 00:44:11.940
theme starting out.
 

00:44:11.940 --> 00:44:20.460
Look at 5:19,
I'm going to back up in a

00:44:20.460 --> 00:44:30.550
minute and go back to some other
dialogues.

00:44:30.550 --> 00:44:33.625
Don't worry I'll finish on time
today but we will probably take

00:44:33.625 --> 00:44:36.550
up again some of the Gospel of
John next time before we talk

00:44:36.550 --> 00:44:38.039
about the letters of John.
 

00:44:38.039 --> 00:44:43.257
5:19:
Jesus said to them,

00:44:43.257 --> 00:44:46.733
"Very truly I tell you,
the Son can do nothing on his

00:44:46.733 --> 00:44:49.539
own but only what he sees the
Father doing.

00:44:49.539 --> 00:44:53.059
For whatever the Father does
the Son does likewise.

00:44:53.059 --> 00:44:56.210
The Father loves the Son and
shows him all that he himself is

00:44:56.210 --> 00:44:56.630
doing.
 

00:44:56.630 --> 00:44:59.677
And he will show him greater
works than these so that you

00:44:59.677 --> 00:45:00.820
will be astonished.
 

00:45:00.820 --> 00:45:03.539
Indeed, just as the Father
raises the dead and gives them

00:45:03.539 --> 00:45:06.309
life, so also the Son gives life
to whomever he wishes.

00:45:06.309 --> 00:45:09.067
The Father judges no one but
has given all judgment to the

00:45:09.067 --> 00:45:11.726
Son so that all may honor the
Son just as they honor the

00:45:11.726 --> 00:45:12.260
Father.
 

00:45:12.260 --> 00:45:15.548
Anyone who does not honor the
Son does not honor the Father

00:45:15.548 --> 00:45:16.400
who sent him.
 

00:45:16.400 --> 00:45:19.204
Very truly I tell you,
anyone who hears my word and

00:45:19.204 --> 00:45:22.456
believes him who sent me has
eternal life and does not come

00:45:22.456 --> 00:45:25.710
unto judgment but has passed
from death to life."

00:45:25.710 --> 00:45:32.590
Look at 5:18,
right before that:

00:45:32.590 --> 00:45:37.460
For this reason the Jews were
seeking all the more to kill him

00:45:37.460 --> 00:45:42.572
because he was not only breaking
the Sabbath but was also calling

00:45:42.572 --> 00:45:44.650
God his own Father....
 

00:45:44.650 --> 00:45:47.347
Now that's so far where you've
gotten in the narrative but

00:45:47.347 --> 00:45:49.289
notice what the author adds
right that.

00:45:49.289 --> 00:45:53.748
The very next phrase,
"thereby making himself

00:45:53.748 --> 00:45:55.659
equal to God."
 

00:45:55.659 --> 00:45:59.639
Is every son always equal to a
father?

00:45:59.639 --> 00:46:04.980
Go like this--nope.
 

00:46:04.980 --> 00:46:08.610
All sons are not equal to all
fathers.

00:46:08.610 --> 00:46:12.291
The Gospel writer is
editorializing because this is

00:46:12.291 --> 00:46:13.690
what he believes.
 

00:46:13.690 --> 00:46:17.557
He believes that not only is
Jesus God's Son in some kind of

00:46:17.557 --> 00:46:21.451
derivative sense,
he believes that by saying that

00:46:21.451 --> 00:46:26.192
Jesus is God's Son,
he's actually equal to God the

00:46:26.192 --> 00:46:26.989
Father.
 

00:46:26.989 --> 00:46:29.726
Look at 8:58,
I'm going to come back and talk

00:46:29.726 --> 00:46:31.469
about chapter 8 next time.
 

00:46:37.219 --> 00:46:41.748
Chapter 8 is one of these
classic scenes in the Gospel of

00:46:41.748 --> 00:46:46.762
John which start out with Jesus
just talking to someone in what

00:46:46.762 --> 00:46:51.210
seems to be a cordial and
relatively peaceful mood.

00:46:51.210 --> 00:46:54.851
Then as the conversation goes
on, things get more and more

00:46:54.851 --> 00:46:57.556
heated,
and people accuse Jesus of

00:46:57.556 --> 00:47:01.539
things but Jesus is just as bad,
he accuses people of stuff all

00:47:01.539 --> 00:47:03.721
the time,
ridiculous stuff sometimes,

00:47:03.721 --> 00:47:05.750
like they're children of Satan.
 

00:47:05.750 --> 00:47:08.429
And the whole thing ends up
with this big division and

00:47:08.429 --> 00:47:11.110
everybody's starting to throw
things at each other.

00:47:11.110 --> 00:47:14.012
Then the next chapter will
start and you'll see them

00:47:14.012 --> 00:47:16.461
talking again,
and again, it comes down to a

00:47:16.461 --> 00:47:17.429
big division.
 

00:47:17.429 --> 00:47:20.804
This is the end of Chapter 8
which is one of these scenes of

00:47:20.804 --> 00:47:23.838
a discussion turning into fight,
turning into a brawl,

00:47:23.838 --> 00:47:25.440
turning into a division.
 

00:47:25.440 --> 00:47:27.039
Where does it end?
 

00:47:27.039 --> 00:47:32.605
Verse 58, chapter 8:
Jesus said to them,

00:47:32.605 --> 00:47:39.159
"Very truly I tell you,
before Abraham was I am."

00:47:39.159 --> 00:47:42.550
So they picked up stones to
throw at him.

00:47:42.550 --> 00:47:47.777
Isn't that interesting,
all he has to say is,

00:47:47.777 --> 00:47:48.610
I am.
 

00:47:48.610 --> 00:47:51.590
Why is that so much of a
problem?

00:47:51.590 --> 00:47:53.757
Where does "I am"
come from?

00:47:53.757 --> 00:47:54.110
Yes.
 

00:47:54.110 --> 00:47:58.389
Student: 
&gt;

00:47:58.389 --> 00:48:00.219
Prof: That's the
declaration of what God is,

00:48:00.219 --> 00:48:01.987
when God says,
"I am,"

00:48:01.987 --> 00:48:03.869
to whom and where in the Bible.
 

00:48:03.869 --> 00:48:04.920
Student:  Moses.
 

00:48:04.920 --> 00:48:07.121
Prof: Moses in front of
the burning bush,

00:48:07.121 --> 00:48:07.590
exactly.
 

00:48:07.590 --> 00:48:10.646
The very name of God,
which those of us who are

00:48:10.646 --> 00:48:13.239
non-Jewish we usually say is
Yahweh,

00:48:13.239 --> 00:48:15.989
there are only four letters in
Hebrew,

00:48:15.989 --> 00:48:19.394
and those four letters don't
have vowels attached to them so

00:48:19.394 --> 00:48:22.050
we're not really sure how to
pronounce them.

00:48:22.050 --> 00:48:24.789
In your English Bible they're
usually translated by

00:48:24.789 --> 00:48:26.599
"Lord"
in small caps.

00:48:26.599 --> 00:48:28.233
Whenever you see
"Lord"

00:48:28.233 --> 00:48:31.297
in small caps in your English
translation of the Hebrew Bible

00:48:31.297 --> 00:48:33.340
that means that the
tetragrammaton,

00:48:33.340 --> 00:48:36.880
the four letters of God's name
are in the Hebrew.

00:48:36.880 --> 00:48:39.539
But according to pious Jewish
usage,

00:48:39.539 --> 00:48:41.936
you never pronounce those,
so you would say something like

00:48:41.936 --> 00:48:43.619
"the Lord"
as a substitute,

00:48:43.619 --> 00:48:45.900
and that's the way in the Greek
Bible it does,

00:48:45.900 --> 00:48:48.429
since the Greek Bible didn't
know what the name was,

00:48:48.429 --> 00:48:50.494
it just would say adonai
or "the Lord"

00:48:50.494 --> 00:48:51.449
or something like that.
 

00:48:51.449 --> 00:48:53.650
And so we would use that in the
English translation.

00:48:53.650 --> 00:48:57.958
The scholars think that perhaps
the best translation for those

00:48:57.958 --> 00:49:01.811
four letters,
as they occur in Exodus,

00:49:01.811 --> 00:49:05.780
is being-ness or "I
am."

00:49:05.780 --> 00:49:09.538
Notice what Jesus is saying,
he's claiming to be the one who

00:49:09.538 --> 00:49:11.639
spoke to Moses out of the bush.
 

00:49:11.639 --> 00:49:14.670
That's radical.
 

00:49:14.670 --> 00:49:17.489
That's way more radical than
anything we've seen in any of

00:49:17.489 --> 00:49:18.480
the other Gospels.
 

00:49:18.480 --> 00:49:23.130
Jesus could be the Son of God
and still not be God.

00:49:23.130 --> 00:49:26.681
Jesus could be the Son of the
Father and still not be equal to

00:49:26.681 --> 00:49:27.440
the Father.
 

00:49:27.440 --> 00:49:31.489
Jesus could be the Messiah and
still not be divine,

00:49:31.489 --> 00:49:35.547
and Jesus could be even the
Messiah and divine and still not

00:49:35.547 --> 00:49:37.059
be "I am."
 

00:49:37.059 --> 00:49:40.090
In the Gospel of John,
nuh-uh, Jesus says "I

00:49:40.090 --> 00:49:42.869
am," he's the one who spoke
to Moses.

00:49:42.869 --> 00:49:46.809
It's no wonder that the Jews
tried to stone him.

00:49:46.809 --> 00:49:49.179
We'll talk about that further
next time.

